I'll sing it.

727
00:30:06,104 --> 00:30:08,339
Your only deed is for you
to get off the phone

728
00:30:08,406 --> 00:30:10,341
and figure out where I'll be
tomorrow night

729
00:30:10,408 --> 00:30:12,843
so you can tell me
what you need to tell me.

730
00:30:12,911 --> 00:30:15,279
Okay, can I just have
some sort of--

731
00:30:15,347 --> 00:30:17,848
Hello?

732
00:30:19,951 --> 00:30:22,119
Good to see you,
Tanner.

733
00:30:22,187 --> 00:30:23,921
Hello, Harvey.

734
00:30:23,972 --> 00:30:25,622
What do you got
in your hand there?

735
00:30:25,690 --> 00:30:27,210
It's an arrest warrant
for your father.

736
00:30:27,225 --> 00:30:29,860
Turns out he did a little
insider trading a few years ago,

737
00:30:29,927 --> 00:30:31,495
and I pulled some strings.

738
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:35,532
- Bullshit.
- You're right, I'm lying,

739
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:37,768
just like Stephen Huntley did
on his affidavit,

740
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:38,836
and we've got proof.

741
00:30:38,903 --> 00:30:40,604
Well, look who decided
to show up.

742
00:30:40,671 --> 00:30:42,873
I was waiting for you
to get some points on the board.

743
00:30:42,941 --> 00:30:44,221
Now we can start
having some fun.

744
00:30:44,275 --> 00:30:46,477
Nice try, Tanner,
but that affidavit was bullshit,

745
00:30:46,544 --> 00:30:48,946
now you got nothing to back up
your bullshit on Scottie.

746
00:30:49,014 --> 00:30:50,114
You think I need backup?

747
00:30:50,165 --> 00:30:51,815
It wasn't about her.
It was about you.

748
00:30:51,883 --> 00:30:53,617
I'm going to drag her ass
through the mud

749
00:30:53,668 --> 00:30:55,786
left, right, and center,
and when I'm done with her,

750
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:59,289
there's not a firm that'll
touch her with a 10-foot pole.

751
00:30:59,340 --> 00:31:01,780
What the hell happened to you?
Why are you doing this, Tanner?

752
00:31:01,793 --> 00:31:03,210
I'm doing it for my client.

753
00:31:03,294 --> 00:31:05,162
You actually had me thinking
if we ever met again--

754
00:31:05,230 --> 00:31:06,363
That I'd fight fair?

755
00:31:06,431 --> 00:31:08,866
I do in the ring,
but this isn't the ring,

756
00:31:08,933 --> 00:31:12,202
and you know very well that you
can stop me anytime you want.

757
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:13,537
If I settle.

758
00:31:13,588 --> 00:31:15,773
There are lot of zeroes
on that offer.

759
00:31:15,840 --> 00:31:18,375
You just need to decide whether
you care more about money

760
00:31:18,443 --> 00:31:21,278
or your girlfriend.

761
00:31:35,910 --> 00:31:38,362
Donna told me that Stephen's
affidavit is dead.

762
00:31:38,430 --> 00:31:41,498
It is, but it doesn't matter,
because Tanner's

763
00:31:41,566 --> 00:31:44,802
gonna keep coming after you
unless we sign this.

764
00:31:46,071 --> 00:31:47,387
You'll never sign this.

765
00:31:47,472 --> 00:31:49,306
Scottie,
you may not believe this,

766
00:31:49,374 --> 00:31:52,042
but if the decision were mine,
I would.

767
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:54,545
Jessica--
she wouldn't even consider it.

768
00:31:54,612 --> 00:31:56,013
I should have known.

769
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:58,348
This is about you getting me
to split you off from Edward

770
00:31:58,416 --> 00:32:00,184
so you can convince Ava
to stop coming after you.

771
00:32:00,251 --> 00:32:02,820
- This isn't about that.
- Then what is it about?

772
00:32:02,887 --> 00:32:05,222
I can't stand to see them
come after you.

773
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,530
- Bullshit!
- It's not bullshit.

774
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:07,724
You think I can't take it!

775
00:32:07,792 --> 00:32:09,476
Look, you're not listening
to me, okay?

776
00:32:09,561 --> 00:32:11,962
I can't take it!

777
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:14,698
Scottie, Tanner can only
come after you

778
00:32:14,765 --> 00:32:16,567
if Ava lets him
come after you,

779
00:32:16,634 --> 00:32:18,795
and Ava's only letting him
come after you to get to me.

780
00:32:18,803 --> 00:32:20,404
Take off the shackles off
and let me convince her

781
00:32:20,472 --> 00:32:22,573
this fight isn't with me,
it's with Edward.

782
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:24,641
Okay, Harvey.

783
00:32:24,692 --> 00:32:27,044
Okay, you win.

784
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:32,382
Shackles are off.

785
00:32:35,370 --> 00:32:36,870
- Hi.
- Hey.

786
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:41,141
There's something that I need
to tell you, and...

787
00:32:41,226 --> 00:32:43,861
I really don't want to.

788
00:32:43,928 --> 00:32:47,147
Okay.
You're scaring me.

789
00:32:47,232 --> 00:32:49,399
Jessica came by my place
this morning.

790
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:52,402
- She knows about us.
- She does.

791
00:32:52,453 --> 00:32:53,937
Okay.

792
00:32:54,005 --> 00:32:55,639
She says that you're
Robert Zane's daughter,

793
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:59,409
and if you want
to stay at the firm...

794
00:32:59,477 --> 00:33:02,146
You need to sign
an affidavit.

795
00:33:02,213 --> 00:33:05,599
Saying what?

796
00:33:05,683 --> 00:33:08,552
That you know I'm a fraud.

797
00:33:11,089 --> 00:33:13,457
Well, what if
I don't sign it?

798
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:15,742
Then she'll fire me.

799
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:18,946
I don't believe that.
You've got leverage.

800
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:22,449
No, that just stops her
from exposing me, not firing me.

801
00:33:22,534 --> 00:33:24,785
- Bullshit.
- No, it's not bullshit.

802
00:33:24,869 --> 00:33:27,788
If she fires me, what am I
gonna to do, run to the D.A.?

803
00:33:27,872 --> 00:33:30,073
Have them throw me in jail
just to get her back?

804
00:33:30,124 --> 00:33:33,377
I'm not going to do that,
and she knows it.

805
00:33:41,269 --> 00:33:45,522
Can't stand that I put you
in this position.

806
00:33:45,590 --> 00:33:48,442
And the only way I can see
out of this is...

807
00:33:48,526 --> 00:33:50,811
for you to go to Stanford.

808
00:33:53,237 --> 00:33:56,088
Miss Hessington, when we first met

809
00:33:56,745 --> 00:33:58,779
did you admit
you bribed a foreign government

810
00:33:58,847 --> 00:33:59,847
to get your pipeline?

811
00:33:59,915 --> 00:34:01,382
I pled guilty.

812
00:34:01,450 --> 00:34:03,751
I didn't ask you
what you pled.

813
00:34:03,819 --> 00:34:05,920
I asked if you did it.
That's privileged.

814
00:34:05,988 --> 00:34:08,256
Your client forfeited
privilege when she sued me.

815
00:34:08,323 --> 00:34:09,423
Keep that in mind.

816
00:34:09,491 --> 00:34:10,591
My client's not suing you.

817
00:34:10,659 --> 00:34:12,360
She's suing
Pearson Darby Specter.

818
00:34:12,427 --> 00:34:15,129
There is no
Pearson Darby Specter.

819
00:34:15,180 --> 00:34:16,664
We split.

820
00:34:16,732 --> 00:34:18,149
Edward Darby
wouldn't allow that.

821
00:34:18,233 --> 00:34:20,074
Edward Darby doesn't have
the power to stop it.

822
00:34:20,135 --> 00:34:22,536
But I do, and I'm not going to
let you make them suffer

823
00:34:22,604 --> 00:34:25,106
for what Darby did.
Hell of a performance, Harvey.

824
00:34:25,173 --> 00:34:26,574
Back-up singers
and everything.

825
00:34:26,642 --> 00:34:27,758
It's still not
going to stop us.

826
00:34:27,843 --> 00:34:30,177
And he isn't
making them suffer.

827
00:34:30,245 --> 00:34:31,846
I am
for what he did to me.

828
00:34:31,914 --> 00:34:34,649
Did what to you?
Get you a slap on the wrist

829
00:34:34,716 --> 00:34:35,850
for your original
bribery charges,

830
00:34:35,918 --> 00:34:37,818
get you off murder,

831
00:34:37,886 --> 00:34:39,453
or stop you
from bribing witnesses?

832
00:34:39,521 --> 00:34:41,255
Which brings me
to my next question.

833
00:34:41,323 --> 00:34:43,491
Did you fire me
for refusing to bribe witnesses

834
00:34:43,542 --> 00:34:44,825
on your behalf?

835
00:34:44,893 --> 00:34:47,128
- You're under oath.
- Don't answer that.

836
00:34:47,195 --> 00:34:48,963
I wouldn't.
It's a federal crime.

837
00:34:49,031 --> 00:34:50,931
She doesn't have to.
Like I said,

838
00:34:50,983 --> 00:34:53,901
we're not bound by privilege
and I've got three witnesses,

839
00:34:53,969 --> 00:34:55,436
including your friend
Stephen Huntley

840
00:34:55,504 --> 00:34:57,622
who testified to it
in open court.

841
00:34:57,706 --> 00:35:00,708
You want to throw stones, Ava?
We've got some rocks of our own.

842
00:35:07,449 --> 00:35:08,949
What are you doing,
Harvey?

843
00:35:09,001 --> 00:35:10,885
I'm talking to your client
off the record.

844
00:35:10,936 --> 00:35:12,720
No, no, no.
On the record, or not at all.

845
00:35:12,788 --> 00:35:13,955
No, let him speak.

846
00:35:14,022 --> 00:35:17,858
I want to hear
what he's got to say.

847
00:35:17,926 --> 00:35:20,995
Ava, you can come at us
and we can come at you.

848
00:35:22,864 --> 00:35:26,100
I don't want that.

849
00:35:26,168 --> 00:35:29,337
You wanted to know if I'm sorry.
I am.

850
00:35:29,404 --> 00:35:32,506
I'm sorry
I didn't listen to you,

851
00:35:32,574 --> 00:35:34,241
I'm sorry
I didn't believe you,

852
00:35:34,309 --> 00:35:36,844
I am sorry that my history
with Cameron

853
00:35:36,912 --> 00:35:38,412
put a target on your back,

854
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:41,349
but I am not sorry that I did
everything in my power

855
00:35:41,416 --> 00:35:43,351
to help you
every chance I got.

856
00:35:43,418 --> 00:35:45,519
If you don't believe that,
then keep coming.

857
00:35:45,587 --> 00:35:50,291
But if you do, I'm asking,
put your anger where it belongs.

858
00:35:57,899 --> 00:36:01,819
Tanner, I hope you still have
that quarter I gave you,

859
00:36:01,903 --> 00:36:04,355
'cause I think it's time
to call your mom.

860
00:36:04,439 --> 00:36:07,408
Harvey.

861
00:36:07,476 --> 00:36:10,878
Fantastic.

862
00:36:24,459 --> 00:36:26,060
I hear we won.

863
00:36:26,128 --> 00:36:27,795
We hit a single.
Just kidding.

864
00:36:27,862 --> 00:36:29,714
We knocked the son of a bitch
out of the park.

865
00:36:29,798 --> 00:36:31,866
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations to you.

866
00:36:31,933 --> 00:36:34,335
I hear you're representing
Stephen Huntley now.

867
00:36:34,402 --> 00:36:37,538
Yeah.
Might as well be.

868
00:36:37,606 --> 00:36:39,140
What's that
supposed to mean?

869
00:36:39,207 --> 00:36:41,475
It means we sat and had drinks
when we thought Ava was guilty.

870
00:36:41,526 --> 00:36:43,744
Now Stephen is.
What's the difference?

871
00:36:43,812 --> 00:36:45,880
Guess your morning off
didn't do the trick.

872
00:36:45,947 --> 00:36:48,182
What are we doing here,
Harvey?

873
00:36:48,250 --> 00:36:51,085
We spend every minute
of our lives in this office

874
00:36:51,153 --> 00:36:53,087
fighting with each other
over meaningless shit

875
00:36:53,155 --> 00:36:54,655
for clients
that we don't even know,

876
00:36:54,723 --> 00:36:56,323
and then when some
real connection comes along,

877
00:36:56,391 --> 00:36:58,926
just some little piece
of happiness--

878
00:37:08,566 --> 00:37:10,420
Mike.

879
00:37:12,524 --> 00:37:15,409
I'm sorry.

880
00:37:20,549 --> 00:37:22,583
Did she tell you
what she did?

881
00:37:22,650 --> 00:37:24,819
Rachel?

882
00:37:24,886 --> 00:37:28,489
I guess not.

883
00:37:28,557 --> 00:37:30,257
Jessica's basically forcing her
to go to Stanford

884
00:37:30,325 --> 00:37:32,026
instead of Columbia.

885
00:37:32,094 --> 00:37:33,928
She found out
about you two.

886
00:37:33,995 --> 00:37:36,931
I don't want her to go.

887
00:37:36,998 --> 00:37:39,767
And there's nothing
I can do about it.

888
00:37:48,076 --> 00:37:49,610
Come in.

889
00:37:53,148 --> 00:37:56,951
I want to talk to you about...
This.

890
00:37:58,420 --> 00:37:59,703
I see you haven't
signed it.

891
00:37:59,788 --> 00:38:01,822
No, I haven't.

892
00:38:01,890 --> 00:38:03,958
Then you must want something,
because you wouldn't be here

893
00:38:04,025 --> 00:38:05,659
just to tell me
you weren't going to sign it.

894
00:38:05,727 --> 00:38:07,628
Mike said you were worried
that Robert Zane's daughter

895
00:38:07,696 --> 00:38:11,332
knew his secret, which got me
thinking about my father

896
00:38:11,399 --> 00:38:13,200
and something
he's always said.

897
00:38:13,268 --> 00:38:14,885
- Which is?
- Don't sign anything

898
00:38:14,970 --> 00:38:16,837
unless you can get something
in return.

899
00:38:16,905 --> 00:38:19,540
- It's called consideration.
- I know what it's called.

900
00:38:23,995 --> 00:38:26,263
What do you want?

901
00:38:26,348 --> 00:38:29,316
You want me to guarantee
that I won't do something

902
00:38:29,384 --> 00:38:30,951
that I would never do.

903
00:38:31,019 --> 00:38:32,979
I want you to guarantee
that you will do something

904
00:38:33,021 --> 00:38:37,024
that you thought you would
never do but should do.

905
00:38:37,091 --> 00:38:39,126
I can't wait to hear this.

906
00:38:39,194 --> 00:38:40,354
Waive the Harvard rule
for me.

907
00:38:40,395 --> 00:38:42,663
- You're not even a lawyer.
- But I will be,

908
00:38:42,731 --> 00:38:44,865
and when I am,
I want to work here.

909
00:38:44,933 --> 00:38:46,567
The Harvard rule

910
00:38:46,634 --> 00:38:48,569
is the longest-standing rule
we have.

911
00:38:48,636 --> 00:38:52,356
I have been killing it here
for the better part of a decade.

912
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:54,608
I'm better than most of
the associates in that bullpen

913
00:38:54,676 --> 00:38:56,877
and I haven't even
gone to law school yet,

914
00:38:56,945 --> 00:38:59,446
so imagine what it'll be like
once I have.

915
00:38:59,514 --> 00:39:01,949
You are
your father's daughter.

916
00:39:02,017 --> 00:39:03,784
Yes, I am.

917
00:39:03,852 --> 00:39:05,402
But I don't want to work
for him.

918
00:39:05,487 --> 00:39:08,322
I want to work for you.

919
00:39:13,494 --> 00:39:15,062
To kicking
Travis Tanner's ass.

920
00:39:15,113 --> 00:39:19,300
You got that right.

921
00:39:19,367 --> 00:39:23,254
Mmm.
A pretty great meal.

922
00:39:23,338 --> 00:39:25,339
Couldn't have done it
without you.

923
00:39:25,406 --> 00:39:27,808
I know, I taught you
how to make it.

924
00:39:27,876 --> 00:39:30,544
Right after we crushed
the bar.

925
00:39:30,612 --> 00:39:34,515
I also remember
what happened later that night.

926
00:39:34,582 --> 00:39:37,484
It was
a pretty great night.

927
00:39:40,005 --> 00:39:43,257
Harvey.

928
00:39:43,325 --> 00:39:44,692
Why am I here?

929
00:39:44,759 --> 00:39:48,028
Well, I haven't cooked
anyone dinner for a while,

930
00:39:48,096 --> 00:39:49,930
and I thought you deserved it.
I did,

931
00:39:49,998 --> 00:39:51,565
but you've made it clear
that you don't want more,

932
00:39:51,633 --> 00:39:54,635
and I don't want to go back
to the way it was, so...

933
00:39:54,703 --> 00:39:57,537
I want to work with you.

934
00:39:58,607 --> 00:40:01,375
What?

935
00:40:01,442 --> 00:40:03,978
You've been associated
with the name Darby too long.

936
00:40:04,045 --> 00:40:05,212
I can help you.

937
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:06,830
I don't need your help.
I'll be fine.

938
00:40:06,915 --> 00:40:08,949
No, you won't,
and all that stuff about Tanner

939
00:40:09,017 --> 00:40:11,051
coming after you and me
not being able to take it,

940
00:40:11,102 --> 00:40:13,187
it was true.
I care about you.

941
00:40:13,255 --> 00:40:16,790
Come to Pearson Specter.
I know that you care about me.

942
00:40:16,858 --> 00:40:18,392
You have made that
very clear,

943
00:40:18,460 --> 00:40:19,760
but I am not interested

944
00:40:19,828 --> 00:40:21,468
in working with someone
day in and day out

945
00:40:21,496 --> 00:40:24,598
where all they can manage to say
is, "I care about you."

946
00:40:24,666 --> 00:40:26,033
- Is that all I've ever said?
- Actually, yes,

947
00:40:26,101 --> 00:40:28,936
over and over again,
"I care about you."

948
00:40:28,987 --> 00:40:30,704
Just what every girl
wants to hear.

949
00:40:30,772 --> 00:40:33,173
- Scottie, that's--
- No, no, no.

950
00:40:39,180 --> 00:40:40,581
If all you want to do
is work with me,

951
00:40:40,649 --> 00:40:42,249
I can find a job
somewhere else.

952
00:40:42,300 --> 00:40:44,218
It's the best I--

953
00:40:46,121 --> 00:40:47,888
Sorry, I should just go.
I don't--

954
00:40:47,955 --> 00:40:53,027
Scottie,
that's not all I want.

955
00:40:53,094 --> 00:40:56,330
Then say it.

956
00:40:56,398 --> 00:40:58,632
I want you in my life.

957
00:41:05,607 --> 00:41:08,442
- Hi.
- Hi.

958
00:41:08,510 --> 00:41:10,177
Thought you didn't like
coming down here.

959
00:41:10,245 --> 00:41:14,014
- Can I come in?
- Yeah, of course.

960
00:41:24,642 --> 00:41:27,661
I finished my list.

961
00:41:27,729 --> 00:41:29,129
And?

962
00:41:29,197 --> 00:41:32,399
Stanford.

963
00:41:32,467 --> 00:41:35,703
It's the better fit.

964
00:41:35,770 --> 00:41:37,171
Rachel, look--

965
00:41:43,244 --> 00:41:45,612
I don't need a list
to tell me

966
00:41:45,680 --> 00:41:48,499
that I don't want to be
without you.

967
00:41:51,653 --> 00:41:53,087
You're staying?

968
00:41:53,154 --> 00:41:55,021
Just try and stop me.

969
00:42:00,628 --> 00:42:01,995
You were messing with me.

970
00:42:02,047 --> 00:42:03,130
- You got me.
- I got...

971
00:42:03,181 --> 00:42:04,331
You!
